          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EDEG",
                "EXTB",
                "GSPEC",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Standard stacked foil irradiation method was used, Al",
                "and Ti foils served as energy degraders and beam",
                "monitors. Irradiations were done in the energy range",
                "from 8 to 35.4 MeV. The beam current was registered by",
                "an integrator, and monitored by Ti monitor foils.",
                "The natTi(3He,x)48V monitor reaction was used.",
                "Irradiation time was 2 h with beam currents of 100 nA.",
                "The energy degradation in the stack was calculated",
                "using the tables of Williamson (see REL-REF).",
                "Gamma spectra were measured non-destructively on a",
                "HPGe detector.",
                "Decay data were taken from WWW Table of Radioactive",
                "Isotopes Browne and Firestone, 1986"
              ]
            }
          ],
